snippet: The spacecraft attracted a parade atmosphere as it drew crowds during its slow trip through city streets to its retirement at the California Science Center.
abstract: Space shuttle Endeavour rolls out of the Los Angeles International Airport for what has been named Mission 26: its two-day crawl through urban streets to retirement at the California Science Center 12 miles away; slow progress attracts a parade atmosphere as thousands gather to watch its final journey.
lead_paragraph: The spacecraft attracted a parade atmosphere as it drew crowds during its slow trip through city streets to its retirement at the California Science Center.
